(2765, 219, 'additional_info', 'Vice President, Engineering and West Coast Operations\r\n\r\nScott Siegler is vice president of engineering and West Coast operations at Gamut. In this capacity, he oversees Gamuts industry-leading real-time pricing (RTP) algorithms to maximize yield for publishers and secure superior audiences for buyers. \r\n\r\nSiegler has extensive experience developing data-driven products at different scales. He previously served as the technology lead at San Francisco-based advertising agencies Agency.com and Signal to Noise for clients including Apple, eBay, and Nike. \r\n\r\nSiegler received a degree in applied mathematics from Queens University in Canada, and completed his doctoral studies in scientific computing and computational mathematics at Stanford University.'),
